### Import Dexie Storage for RxDB

Source: https://github.com/pubkey/rxdb/blob/master/docs/rx-storage-dexie.html

Imports the necessary functions from RxDB to create a database with the Dexie storage plugin. This is the initial step for using Dexie with RxDB.

```javascript
import { createRxDatabase } from 'rxdb/plugins/core';
import { getRxStorageDexie } from 'rxdb/plugins/storage-dexie';
```

--------------------------------

### Create RxDB Database with Dexie Storage

Source: https://github.com/pubkey/rxdb/blob/master/docs/rx-storage-dexie.html

Initializes an RxDB database using the Dexie storage engine. This function sets up the database instance with a specified name, ready for collections to be added.

```javascript
const db = await createRxDatabase({
  name: 'mydb',
  storage: getRxStorageDexie()
});
```

--------------------------------

### AsyncStorage-Down Adapter Setup for RXDB

Source: https://github.com/pubkey/rxdb/blob/master/docs-src/docs/adapters.md

This configuration enables RXDB to use AsyncStorage as a leveldown-compatible storage. It requires the 'pouchdb-adapter-asyncstorage-down' and 'pouchdb-adapter-leveldb' plugins. The 'asyncstorage-down' module is passed directly as the storage option.

```javascript
// npm install pouchdb-adapter-asyncstorage-down --save
addPouchPlugin(require('pouchdb-adapter-leveldb')); // leveldown adapters need the leveldb plugin to work

const asyncstorageDown = require('asyncstorage-down');

const database = await createRxDatabase({
    name: 'mydatabase',
    storage: getRxStoragePouch(asyncstorageDown) // the full leveldown-module
});
```

--------------------------------

### RxDB IndexedDB Browser Storage Adapter

Source: https://github.com/pubkey/rxdb/blob/master/docs/adapters.html

Illustrates the setup for using the IndexedDB adapter with RxDB in browser environments. This adapter leverages the browser's native IndexedDB API for data storage. Ensure 'pouchdb-adapter-idb' is installed and added as a PouchDB plugin.

```javascript
// npm install pouchdb-adapter-idb --save
addPouchPlugin(require('pouchdb-adapter-idb'));

const database = await createRxDatabase({
    name: 'mydatabase',
    storage: getRxStoragePouch('idb')
});
```

