### RxDB Memory Storage Adapter Example

Source: https://github.com/pubkey/rxdb/blob/master/docs/adapters.html

Demonstrates how to create an RxDatabase using the memory adapter for PouchDB. This adapter stores data in JavaScript runtime memory, offering high performance but no persistence. It's ideal for testing or scenarios where data loss is acceptable upon process termination.

```javascript
import { createRxDatabase } from 'rxdb';
import { getRxStoragePouch } from 'rxdb/plugins/pouchdb';

// npm install pouchdb-adapter-memory --save
addPouchPlugin(require('pouchdb-adapter-memory'));

const database = await createRxDatabase({
    name: 'mydatabase',
    storage: getRxStoragePouch('memory')
});
```

